review_blob: I am partial to this beer. One of my favourite southern Ontario craft beers. Strong aroma, with an intense sweet or fruity taste. Plenty of character although discourages those looking for a hoppy taste. Enjoyable.
Unfortunately other than its appearance and colour, I found this red to be somewhat disappointing. Expected more of an intense taste and aroma. Others do this better.

Nice colour and pleasant taste. Noticeable aroma when bought in bottle although less so when from can who knows?. Has hints of rye flavour, which may actually be this beers best attribute. One of my favourite go to beers.
Nice colour and pleasant aroma. Somewhat overwhelming carbonization although easy to drink. Nothing to special, but enjoyable.
